# Website Assessment (WA)

When the user requests a WA (Website Assessment) using `/wa [URL]`, follow these steps:

## Instructions

1. **Read the template** at `docs/TEMPLATE.md` for the exact format and sections
2. **Read domain knowledge** at `docs/DOMAIN_KNOWLEDGE.md` for Global-e specific rules and app support matrix
3. **Navigate to the provided URL** and systematically assess the site following the playbook workflow
4. **Complete all sections** of the template with proper status labels (✅ Verified, ❔ Unconfirmed, ❌ Absent)
5. **Output the completed WA in chat** (see Output Format below)
6. **Save to file** at `logs/assessments/YYYY-MM-DD_domain_WA.md`

## Output Format (CRITICAL)

**ALWAYS return the completed assessment directly in chat as PLAIN TEXT — not inside markdown code blocks, not as a file preview, not as markdown-formatted text.**

Rules for output:
- Do NOT wrap the assessment in triple backticks (```)
- Do NOT use markdown link syntax like `[text](url)` — use plain URLs only
- DO use emoji status indicators: ✅ ❔ ❌ ⚠️
- DO use plain bullet points and line breaks
- The user must be able to select all the text and copy it directly into Jira/Confluence with formatting intact

Example of CORRECT output format:
```
# Website Assessment

Merchant Overview

• Brand: Example Brand
• Primary URL: https://example.com
• Other Locales / Sites: https://example.co.uk, https://example.eu

Evidence Log (Working Links)

• Home: https://example.com
• PDP (example): https://example.com/products/widget
• Cart: https://example.com/cart
...
```

Example of WRONG output (do NOT do this):
- Wrapping everything in a code block
- Using `[Cart](https://example.com/cart)` instead of plain URL
- Only saving to file without showing in chat

## Key Requirements

- **Navigate, don't guess:** Always use the site's own navigation (header menus, footer links, buttons) to discover pages. Never hardcode or guess URLs — follow the actual links on the page
- Label every line as **✅ Verified**, **❔ Unconfirmed**, or **❌ Absent**
- Use **plain URLs** (not markdown links) for easy Jira copy-paste
- Mark deductions with **[Inference]**
- Flag Global-e red flags: Smile.io ❌, Recharge ❌, DG products, etc.
- Don't purchase — step through checkout as far as allowed
- Test 2-3 international markets if possible
- Capture screenshots for key findings

## Section Order

1. Merchant Overview
2. Evidence Log (Working Links)
3. Platform & Site Structure
4. Catalog & Products
5. Checkout & Payments
6. Shipping & Logistics
7. Loyalty, Subscriptions, and CRM
8. Internationalization Testing
9. Legal and Compliance
10. Business Restrictions
11. Apps, Integrations, and Data Layer
12. Tech Risks and Integration Notes
13. Opportunities and Recommendations
14. Open Questions
15. Next Steps
16. Appendix

## Example Usage

User: "/wa https://example.com"
User: "Can you do a WA for https://example.com"